## [1.10.1] - 2026-04-02

- Wordpress admin notices displayed next to the main headline on the settings page bugfix.

## [1.10.0] - 2026-04-02

- Added "Filtered" status for emails that match filter rules set to "Do Not Send" action.
- Email logs now display the "filtered" status with distinct styling.
- Status donut chart includes "filtered" count.
- Database migration automatically adds the new status to existing installations.

## [1.9.0] - 2026-03-31

- Added "Enable email scheduler" option in General Settings. When disabled, emails are sent immediately instead of being queued (default: enabled).
- Added new "Filters" tab for email filtering rules.
- Filters allow matching emails by subject, body, or recipient using plain text or regex patterns.
- Filter actions: Bypass Scheduling (send immediately), Do Not Send (discard), Set Priority (custom queue priority).
- Filter rules can be prioritized, enabled/disabled individually.
- Added Slovak translations for new features.

## [1.8.1] - 2024-11-13

- Added an authentication mode selector for SMTP profiles with support for password-less (trusted relay) connections.
- Skipped username/password validation when authentication is set to none.
- Mailer now disables SMTP authentication and clears credentials for password-less profiles.

## [1.8.0] - 2024-11-12
- Initial public release with SMTP profile management, queuing, retries, and logging.
